article.headline: Saint Peter's takes down UMBC 69-61
article.description: — Marcus Randolph scored 19 points as Saint Peter's beat UMBC 69-61 on Saturday.
article.story: BALTIMORE -- — Marcus Randolph scored 19 points as Saint Peter's beat UMBC 69-61 on Saturday. Randolph added six rebounds for the Peacocks (1-3). Bryce Eaton shot 5 of 10 from the field, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line to add 14 points. Armoni Zeigler had 12 points and went 5 of 12 from the field (2 for 5 from 3-point range). Bryce Johnson led the way for the Retrievers (3-2) with 15 points. Marlon Short added 12 points and eight rebounds for UMBC. Josh Odunowo finished with 10 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
